HEADWORD: Hydrogalvanic
<hw>Hy`dro*gal*van"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>galvanic</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining
to, produced by, or consisting of, electricity evolved by the action or
use of fluids; <as>as, <ex>hydrogalvanic</ex> currents</as>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
